re the vast majority of the FV community (there will always be an exception or two) feels welcome.  Considering the diverse nature of Fivriona Vie, and the high expectations we all brought to this server and that we still have, keeping most of the people happy even most of the time is a hell of an accomplishment.  My hat is off to Jaxy for bringing this together, and thanks again for trusting me enough to moderate it.<br><br>Now then, moderating isn't easy at the best of times, and it sure hasn't been easy lately.  I think all the moderators here have said a few things lately they'd like to take back. I know I have.  But more than anything I'd like to get things back on track.  So here is what I am asking of everyone.  And I hope I still have the credibility around here to have these requests honored.<br><br>To all board users:  Please bear with us for a bit, and try to be nice to each other.  None of us want to moderate this board to death and I still believe that in a mature community of adults (even if you really aren't an adult, try to RP one) a board such as this one shouldn't need much moderation.  And please try to refrain from being too critical of the moderation here for just a bit, as we sort it out ourselves.  I normally welcome active feedback and polite criticism of all sorts, but the moderators are human too, and have a few bruised feelings right now.  Just give us a standing eight count and let us catch our breath.<br><br>To all moderators:  Please go to, and use, the moderator forum.  That's what it's there for, and it's been drasticly underused.  Whatever minor disagreements we may have certainly don't need to be sorted out in public right here.<br><br>That's all, and thanks in advance to everyone.  I'm damn proud of the FV community, and I'm very pleased we all have a board we can feel comfortable at and call home.  See you all soon.<br><br>Valquiss<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPubli